          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "MASSP",
                "STTA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " After a cooling period of greater than",
                "two months, the foils were melted in a closed,",
                "evacuated system to release the rare gases. The rare",
                "gas fraction was purified and introduced to the",
                "spectrometer for a mass analysis in the static mode.",
                "The mass spectrometer was an ultra-high vacuum 6-in.",
                "radius, 60-deg-sector, single direction focusing",
                "instrument which employed an electron multiplier ion",
                "detector for high sensitivity. The Kr yields in these",
                "experiments were measured relative to the 84Kr chain",
                "yield. The 85Kr (ten-year) relative to 84Kr was",
                "corrected for any decay of the ten-year Kr. From the",
                "relative chain yields of 83Kr, 84Kr, and 86Kr, it is",
                "possible to derive the chain yield for 85Kr by",
                "interpolation."
              ]
            }
          ],
